commit 054990ae8f4154871552ef9e3d23bed8e2083685
Author: rpm-build <rpm-build>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 16:35:54 2026 +0200

    ssl: fix compilation against OpenSSL 4.x
    
    OpenSSL 4 (like 3.x) treats ASN1_* types as opaque and returns
    const pointers from many X509/NAME/EXTENSION accessors.
    
    - Make q_* wrapper declarations and DEFINEFUNC expansions
      const-correct for the affected getters.
    - Add q_ASN1_STRING_type() wrapper.
    - Update read-only ASN1_STRING helpers to accept const.
    - Replace all direct member access (.length, .data, .type) on
      ASN1_TIME/INTEGER/OCTET_STRING etc. with the q_ accessor
      functions.
    - Propagate const through a few private helpers.
    
    This resolves the build failure with -openssl-linked against
    OpenSSL 4.0+ while preserving compatibility with older
    versions.

